TWO PEOPLE lost their lives and a third was injured when the SUV they were in rolled down an embankment before coming to a rest on train tracks on the N2 near the M25 KwaMashu off-ramp in Durban on Sunday.Netcare 911 spokesperson Shawn Herbst said the accident occurred at just after 6.30am on Sunday morning.Herbst said reports indicated that the driver of the SUV lost control which resulted in the vehicle crashing through the safety barriers.He said the vehicle rolled down an embankment about 15 metres and it came to rest on railway tracks below.“When medics arrived on scene, they found that the occupants had been thrown from the vehicle.MORE ON THISTwo people killed in separate crashes on the M7Road Accident Fund asks court to block making audit report public’I fell asleep at the wheel’, says former schoolboy who ploughed into municipal workers, killing one“On assessment, medics found that an adult male and adult female had sustained fatal injuries and were declared deceased on the scene,” said Herbst.Herbst said there was a third patient, an adult male, who had sustained moderate to serious injuries.“The third patient… was treated on scene before being taken by ambulance to hospital,” he said.TWO PEOPLE were killed and a third was injured when the SUV they were travelling in rolled down a bank and on to train tracks on the N2 near the M25 KwaMashu off-ramp in Durban.  |  Netcare 911TWO PEOPLE were killed and a third was injured when the SUV they were travelling in rolled down a bank and on to train tracks on the N2 near the M25 KwaMashu off-ramp in Durban.  |  Netcare 911TWO PEOPLE were killed and a third was injured when the SUV they were travelling in rolled down a bank and on to train tracks on the N2 near the M25 KwaMashu off-ramp in Durban.  |  Netcare 911TWO PEOPLE were killed and a third was injured when the SUV they were travelling in rolled down a bank and on to train tracks on the N2 near the M25 KwaMashu off-ramp in Durban.  |  Netcare 911THE MERCURY